THROUGH 2009, OUR ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT HAS ALWAYS COMPLETED THE ANNUAL REPORT FOR GAS DISTRIBUTION. WE SUBMITTED A TOTAL OF 629 MILES OF MAIN IN PART B ON THE 2009 ANNUAL REPORT WHICH CAME FROM THE INVENTORY CHECKED OUT OF OUR SYSTEM THROUGH THE YEARS. WE NOW HAVE AN UP-TO-DATE GEOGRAPHIC INFORMATION SYSTEM (GIS) THAT WE CONSIDER TO BE MORE ACCURATE AND IT SHOWS THAT WE ACTUALLY ONLY HAD 589 MILES OF MAIN THROUGH 2009. IN RECENT YEARS, MANY REHAB PROJECTS HAVE TAKEN PLACE WHERE WE HAVE REPLACED STEEL MAIN WITH PE MAIN AND WE BELIEVE SOME OF THE ABANDONED PIPE WAS NOT ACCOUNTED FOR WHEN REPORTING. TO CORRECT THIS PROBLEM, WE ARE CHANGING OUR MILES OF MAIN IN PART B #1, 2, AND 4 TO THE FOOTAGES WE HAVE IN OUR GIS. THE 2000-2009 MILES OF MAIN IN PART B #4 WILL BE CHANGED FROM 266 TO 226 TO MAKE THE TOTAL MILES OF MAIN IN PART B #1 & 2 MATCH PART B #4. THIS ADJUSTMENT OF 40 MILES IS BEING MADE DURING THE DECADE WHEN WE PERFORMED THE MAJORITY OF OUR REHAB WORK.
